Theme palettes

Several of the built-in themes in src/themes/builtin.ts are ports of color
schemes published by other projects, each under the MIT License. Dumont bundles
no code from any of them: what is reproduced is the palette, adapted to Dumont's
own tokens, and in places adjusted to meet a WCAG AA contrast floor the original
does not hold to. The themes are named after the schemes they follow so that
users can find them; none of these projects is affiliated with or endorses
Dumont.

    Dracula      Copyright (c) 2016 Dracula Theme
                 https://github.com/dracula/dracula-theme
    Solarized    Copyright (c) 2011 Ethan Schoonover
                 https://github.com/altercation/solarized
    Nord         Copyright (c) 2016-present Sven Greb
                 https://github.com/nordtheme/nord
    Catppuccin   Copyright (c) 2021-present Catppuccin
                 https://github.com/catppuccin/catppuccin

The Visual Studio 2017 theme follows the default colors of Microsoft Visual
Studio, which is not an open-source project; it is an independent reproduction
